An urgent search has been launched to find a missing mum and her baby. There is concern for the welfare of Kirsty, 31, after she left home unexpectedly. Police believe she may be in south Bristol, although officers have not given any information about where she vanished from. Anyone who sees Kirsty and her child has been urged to call 999. The mother is described as white and about 5ft 4ins tall. She has brown eyes, freckles and long brown hair. The registration plate of her grey Astra – PN59 GXW – has been released in an effort to help find her. Avon and Somerset made an appeal on social media, saying: ‘Kirsty, if you see this, please get in touch. We and your family are worried about you and want to help.’ They added: ‘Anyone who sees her is urged to call 999 immediately and quote reference number 5222134373. ‘Anyone who knows where she might be can call 101.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.